"'''Chessa's Doom'''" is a short story written by [[Peter M. Schweighofer]] with illustrations by [[John Paul Lona]]. It was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 1|''Star Wars Adventure Journal 1'']] in [[February]] [[1994]] by [[West End Games]] before being made available online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club]] in [[January]] [[2008]]

It is notable in that parts of the narrative are told in prose and parts are told in textless comic book style illustrations.

==Plot summary==
In the [[Gorkin's Rest]] [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] on [[Wroona/Legends|Wroona]], [[Dirk Harkness]] tells the story of how he became involved with the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. Following the [[Death/Legends|death]] of his lover, [[Chessa Dohhenty]] in a firefight with [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] checking their cargo, Harkness attempts to drown his sorrows in alcohol. As he stares at his reflection in the mirror, he realizes how lost he has become. Just then, a man approaches him, claiming to be a friend of Chessa's. The man reveals himself to be [[General/Legends|General]] [[Halomar Corros|Corros]] and introduces Harkness to the Rebellion.

